    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>ISSUE TYPE: Story</p>

<p>Summary: Investigate and fix Docker data storage to enable local persistence</p>

<p>Description:</p>

<p>Objective<br/>
The application is currently storing data inside the Docker environment instead of on the local machine. The goal is to investigate the root cause and adjust the configuration so that data is stored persistently on the host system.</p>

<p>Context<br/>
Storing data only inside the container can lead to data loss when the container is removed or rebuilt. Proper persistence outside the container must be ensured.</p>

<p>Scope of Work</p>

<p>Andrés is responsible for:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Analyzing the current Docker configuration (Dockerfile, docker-compose, volumes).</li>
	<li>Identifying why data is stored only inside the container.</li>
	<li>Evaluating whether volumes are properly configured.</li>
	<li>Implementing persistent volumes or bind mounts to the host system.</li>
	<li>Verifying storage paths within the application.</li>
	<li>Validating data persistence after restarting or rebuilding containers.</li>
	<li>Documenting the implemented solution.</li>
</ul>


<p>Acceptance Criteria</p>

<ul>
	<li>Root cause of internal container storage is identified.</li>
	<li>Data is stored on the local host system.</li>
	<li>Data persists after stopping, restarting, or rebuilding containers.</li>
	<li>No existing functionality is broken.</li>
	<li>Technical documentation is updated.</li>
</ul>


<p>Definition of Done (DoD)</p>

<ul>
	<li>Docker configuration updated and validated.</li>
	<li>Persistence tests completed successfully.</li>
	<li>Code Review approved.</li>
	<li>Technical documentation updated.</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
